'''Avé''', ('''vierbe''' / ''verb'' / ''verbo''): *to have *avere
== Usage Note == This verb is the most commonly used auxilliary (along with [[Molisan/verbs/èsse|èsse]]). It is not directly synonomous to the Italian verb ''avere'' in other cases. Rather, the verb [[Molisan/verbs/tené|tené]] is used. Avé is never used as a main verb, it only exists as a "helping verb". It is often marked with a silent initial 'h' as in Italian. It is also an essential part of the verb [[Molisan/Verbs/Avé da|avé da]] (dovere, to need to).
== Main declensions == {| class="wikitable" |- | !Presende !Mberfette !Passate Cuembuošte !Cuendeziunale & Uettative !Špecuelative !Mberative |- !ij |align="center" | haje - heje |align="center" | heve |align="center" | haje avute |align="center" | avésse |align="center" | arraje - arreje |align="center" | - |- !tu |align="center" | hi |align="center" | hive |align="center" | hi avute |align="center" | avisse |align="center" | arrì |align="center" | - |- !isse / ésse |align="center" | ha |align="center" | heve |align="center" | ha avute |align="center" | avésse |align="center" | arrà |align="center" | - |- !nuje |align="center" | heme |align="center" | havame |align="center" | heme avute |align="center" | avésseme - avassime |align="center" | arrassime |align="center" | - |- !vuje |align="center" | hete |align="center" | havate |align="center" | hete avute |align="center" | avassite |align="center" | arrassite |align="center" | - |- !lore |align="center" | hanne - henne |align="center" | hàvene |align="center" | hanne avute |align="center" | avéssene |align="center" | arranne |align="center" | - |}
{{BookCat}}
== Other forms == The various tenses of the verb avé can be combined with other verbs' participles to create many different verbal times:
*'''Hi magnate'''. (You '''have eaten''') *'''Hive magnate'''. (You '''had eaten''') *'''Avisse magnate''' nzi mmó. (You '''would have eaten''' by now.) *'''Arrì magnate''' ggia. (You '''might have eaten''' by now.)*rarely used, often replaced by conditional.

